data.title: Network of Graham Stokoe, Analysis of 50 relations
data.meta_description: Identify the source of Graham Stokoe's network. Among these 1 positions of which Corporate Officer/Principal at Ernst & Young LLP, he knows 50 people directly.
data.text:
Miscellaneous Commercial ServicesCommercial Services

Central Houston, Inc. engages in the collaboration and implementation of solutions for the challenges of the city. It focuses on the redevelopment and revitalization by enhancing collaboration among public officials, developers, and businesses. The company was founded in 1983 and is headquartered in Houston, TX.

Miscellaneous Commercial ServicesCommercial Services

The American Institute of Certified Public Accountants provides vocational education in accounting. The company provides services to the accounting community, regulatory bodies, and other organizations. It also operates in Jersey City, Washington, and Lewisville. It was founded in 1887 and is headquartered in New York City, NY.

Services to the Health IndustryHealth Services

United Way of Greater Houston provides child and family social services. It offers programs in the following four areas, developing children and youth to their full potential with an emphasis on programs involving abuse and neglect, adoption, character development, child care and after school services, delinquency intervention, foster care, special education, and teen pregnancy. The company is headquartered in Houston, TX.

Miscellaneous Commercial ServicesCommercial Services

Community Living Mississauga operates as a charitable organization which provides support to people who have an intellectual disability. The company was founded in 1955 and is headquartered in Mississauga, Canada.

Miscellaneous Commercial ServicesCommercial Services

Philadelphia Youth Network, Inc. operates a portfolio of programs that address the skills gap for vulnerable young people. It makes connections among individuals, organizations and systems. The company was founded in 1998 and is headquartered in Philadelphia, PA.

Construction MaterialsNon-Energy Minerals

Oglebay Norton Co. LLC engages in mining, processing, transporting and marketing industrial minerals and aggregates. It provides aggregates and industrial minerals for applications in the building materials, environmental, energy and industrial markets. The company operates in three segments: Great Lakes Minerals, Global Stone and Performance Minerals. The Great Lakes Minerals segment mines and distributes limestone from facilities located in northern Michigan. The Global Stone segment supplies lime, crushed and ground limestone, construction aggregates and chemical limestone in the Great Lakes region. It's products are used as a filler in building materials, waste water treatment and soil stabilization and as an aggregate for construction of highways, shopping centers, hospitals and schools. Performance Minerals segment mines and processes industrial sands. The company was founded in 1854 and is headquartered in Cleveland, OH.

HomebuildingConsumer Durables

Catalyst Housing Ltd. operates as a housing association, which engages in the provision of homes for rent; and home ownership opportunities including shared ownership, outright sales, and equity loans. The company was founded in 1960 and is headquartered in London, the United Kingdom.

Information Technology ServicesTechnology Services

Part of Ernst & Young Global Ltd., Ernst & Young Ltd. (New Zealand) is a New Zealander company that offers legal managed services to address contracting, regulatory compliance, entity governance, and legal operations challenges. The company is based in Auckland, New Zealand. The company also has CCaSS teams that assist in reducing the risk of EHS incidents and support decision-making to improve outcomes associated with EHS. The CEO of the company is Carmine di Sibio.

Miscellaneous Commercial ServicesCommercial Services

The Greater Washington Partnership is a nonprofit alliance of influential and leading employers in the Washington D.C. area. The private company is based in Washington. The American company's goal is to ensure the entire region remains economically competitive and prosperous for all, with the aim of making it the world's best place to live, work, and build a business. The company was founded in 2016 by Russ Ramsey, Ted J. Leonsis, Peter L Scher, and Grant Lovely VerStandig. JB Holston has been the CEO of the company since 2020.

Other Consumer ServicesConsumer Services

Ernst & Young Global Ltd. engages in the provision consulting services. Its services include assurance, consulting, strategy and transaction, and tax. The company was founded on November 26, 2001 and is headquartered in London, the United Kingdom.

Food: Specialty/CandyConsumer Non-Durables

S. & D. Coffee, Inc. manufactures and supplies coffee and tea to restaurants and convenience stores. It offers fresh brewed, specialty, and single cup coffee, liquid coffee concentrate, coffee procurement, and coffee roasting and blending. It also offers fresh brewed ice tea, liquid tea concentrate, hot tea, and tea procurement and blending. The company was founded by J. Roy Davis, Sr. and Lawrence Switzer in 1927 and is headquartered in Concord, NC.

Miscellaneous Commercial ServicesCommercial Services

ZS Associates, Inc. engages in the sales and marketing consulting, outsourcing, technology and software services. Its services include market segmentation, targeting, mergers, integration, forecasting and design. The company was founded by Prabhakant K. Sinha and Andy Zoltners in 1983 and is headquartered in Evanston, IL.

Miscellaneous Commercial ServicesCommercial Services

Deloitte Consulting LLP provides business consulting services. It offers services related to public finance, public sector management, health and social protection, information technology, financial sector, and trade and investment. The company was founded in 1996 and is headquartered in New York, NY.

Data Processing ServicesTechnology Services

TierPoint LLC engages in the provision of connected data center and cloud solutions. It offers services relating to colocation, cloud platforms, network services, security and compliance, disaster recovery, consulting services, and managed services. The company was founded in July 2010 and is headquartered in St. Louis, MO.

Miscellaneous Commercial ServicesCommercial Services

The Business Council of New York State, Inc. is a non-profit organization which provides an array of news and updates, webinars, seminars, networking, and individualized regulatory and legislative assistance for the large and small firms throughout the state. It offers group insurance programs, member discounts, information resources, and publications. The organization was founded in 1980 and is headquartered in New York, NY.

Insurance Brokers/ServicesFinance

RenaissanceRe Syndicate Management Ltd. operates as a managing agent for RenaissanceRe Syndicate 1458. It manages the syndicate, employs the underwriting staff, and oversees the compliance, legal, human resources, modeling, actuarial, and finance functions providing services to the syndicate. The company was founded on June 28, 1973 and is headquartered in London, the United Kingdom.

Engineering & ConstructionIndustrial Services

Malmqvist & Co. Byggnads AB is a Swedish company based in Stockholm, Sweden that specializes in commercial properties. The private company carry out various forms of contracts with a focus on sustainability and high-quality delivery. The company was founded by Samir Gerdtsson and has been led by CEO Simon Becker since 2022.
